 FT922-3171 _AN-CFLAVAECFT 920612 FT 12 JUN 92 / World Trade News: US political sands shift under Nafta - Prospects for the free trade deal are no longer so certain By NANCY DUNNE JUST weeks ago, the prospects for the North American free trade agreement seemed assured.
 The proposed pact between the US, Canada and Mexico had the support of the Republican establishment, of Governor Bill Clinton, the prospective Democratic nominee, of the powerful Texas Democrats on Capitol Hill and most of the Democratic leadership in Congress.
